snippet.textDisplay: Please do a VFX Artists React to 'The Mandalorian'. I know they built a lot of the stages for real but in some cases there are big animated rooms and all the reflections on the helmet and the armor seem to match while in others like in Episode 5, right after he lands and exits the plane you can see some green reflections on his armor although the whole scene is in yellow colors only. And in episode 6 he is in this big hangar with a lot of details while his helmet shows these light sources from the ceiling that I can't seem to find in the scene. Really looks like they dropped an HDRI map onto a cg-animated helmet there but I'm not sure. Would be nice if you could do some suggestions on the various scenes.
snippet.textOriginal: Please do a VFX Artists React to 'The Mandalorian'. And in episode 6 he is in this big hangar with a lot of details while his helmet shows these light sources from the ceiling that I can't seem to find in the scene. snippet.textDisplay:
Another thing that bugs me. In the Transformer movies, why is the bad guys always bigger than the good guys? If they can actually scan another vehicle and transform into it like Bumblebee, why don't all of them do it?
Why not scan something and become bigger, or an airplane or just something else? Why would you stay that shape if your ass is always being kicked?

Like in the second movie, the old Transformer with the cane. Why doesn't he just transform into something new like Bumblebee did?
And last thing, the whole conflict took part somewhere in the galaxy very far from earth. So why do they look like vehicles from earth before they even knew or came to earth?
